track_notes:
This track is the Dublin Trail. Trail length is about 2.6 miles with 1700 feet elevation gain. The trail is not as busy as the trails leading from the visitors center and is a good choice.

Ample parking is available on Old Troy Road at the spot indicated and is well marked. Although Google Maps shows Old Troy Road does not connect to Old Dublin road in fact they do so it is possible to approach the parking area from either direction. The parking lot is large and has maps and a port-o-potty. Be advised this road is not maintained in the winter.

Trail condition is typical for the area, the first half is relatively easy, the second half is quite steep in places.

The summit is bald and although there is plenty of room to install an antenna finding a spot to anchor or hold a mast can be challenging.

When they say this is the second most hiked mountain in the world I would have to say that is true. Early in the day was quiet going up the white dot trail. But coming down mid day there was a lot of hikers on the trail. The White cross trail on the return trip is a good idea.
